into the ecological marvels of another time. A fascinating adventure story of one man’s life in paleoecology, Back to the Future in the Caves of Kaua‘i reveals the excitement-and occasional frustrations-of a career spent exploring what the past can tell us about the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCaveszHawaiizKauai. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zHawaiizKauai. 0aHuman ecologyzHawaiizKauaixHistory. 0aNaturexEffect of human beings onzHawaiizKauaixHistory. 0aPaleoecologyzHawaiizKauai. 0aPrehistoric peopleszHawaiizKauai. 0aTimexPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016311740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300163117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300163117/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles